<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-449] In multi-module projects, all tests are run for each module in the module tree</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-449</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In a multi-module project, since version 2.4, all tests of all modules are run once for each module. This is &lt;b&gt;very&lt;/b&gt; bad with many modules &amp;amp; many tests. Attached is a sample project which contains a parent module and two child modules. Each of the child modules contains one JUnit test. mvn clean site runs each test three times (once for the parent and once for each of the two submodules). When changing the surefire-report-plugin to version 2.3, each test is run only once, as it is supposed to&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Maven 2.0.8, Linux</environment>
        <key id="12810133">SUREFIRE-449</key>
            <summary>In multi-module projects, all tests are run for each module in the module tree</summary>
